name: Festival of Remembrance 2024
summary: Remembrance Sunday 2024 will commemorate the sacrifices of the armed forces and those who have served. The National Service of Remembrance will take place at The Cenotaph and will be broadcast live on the BBC, along with the Royal British Legion's Festival of Remembrance. Senior royals, including the Princess of Wales, attended the Festival of Remembrance, which marked a significant step in her return to public duties. The Princess of Wales honored Princess Diana by wearing her pearl earrings to the event, which was held in the heart of a city to commemorate the armed forces. Princess Kate also made a notable appearance at the Festival of Remembrance, making her first high-profile appearance since her engagement ring was first seen in months. The Queen Consort, Camilla, was forced to withdraw from the event, while Princess Kate looked well-dressed despite her absence.

summary: Bangladesh and Afghanistan have concluded their One Day International (ODI) series, with each team winning a match. In the first ODI, Afghanistan's spinner Ghazanfar took six wickets to lead his team to a 92-run victory. However, Bangladesh bounced back in the second ODI, with Najmul Hossain Shanto scoring a century to help his team win by 68 runs and level the series at 1-1. The final ODI of the series will be played in Sharjah.
